&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ambulatory Care&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The innovative AC service delivers treatments that have historically been delivered in the in-patient setting such as HBSCTs, low intensity Allogeneic BMTs, CAR T cells and various intensive chemotherapy regimens, including haematology and sarcoma protocols. Eligible patients attend the AC bay on a daily basis for assessment and treatment and while clinically well, they reside at either our local hotel or their home address.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ambulatory Care Deputy Sister/Charge Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Within this role, the successful applicant will demonstrate excellent clinical leadership and communication skills and will be responsible for supporting the unit manager with the co-ordination of the service. He/she must be an experienced Haemato-Oncology Nurse who is proficient in all aspects of chemotherapy administration and patient education. They must possess an expert level of knowledge and skills in all areas of IV administration and be expert in Cannulation and Venepuncture. The candidate is required to be proficient in the care of the BMT patients and administration of all forms of cellular return.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, please contact Amy Colada 07946535703 or email: amy.colada@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
